title: Cafe Nissi
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, Buffet, Fast food, Take-out, Guatemalan, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Cafeteria style eatery in the university offering vegetarian items on the steam tray. It's the only place like it on the campus. You can put together a plate with salads, steamed vegetable, stir frys, rice and beans, potatos, fruit, and a drink. Costs around 18-20 Quetzales for a plate (under US$3).
streetAddress: University of San Carlos, bottom floor building T2 (Architecture)
